The paper proposes a new approach for representation learning on graphs using attention and neighborhood aggregation. This is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions experiments involving node classification, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
